The paper deals with the task of sarcasm detection in text, which is a natural language processing problem. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper proposes a hybrid neural network architecture with attention mechanism, which involves training a model on a dataset and optimizing its parameters, making it a machine learning problem. This suggests that the paper could also belong to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also involves experiments and evaluation of the proposed model, which could place it in the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
